						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. 2) beside the ruined Śiva temple on the road-side.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kāma Vaidumba 8th-9th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged hero-stone records the death of a hero while fighting with Vikramayya. The king Kāma-Vaidumba is described as <hi rend="italic">mahārā[jādhi]rāja</hi> and <hi rend="italic">paramēśvara.</hi> There is a mention of Koṇḍu[vu]ra Narapa • • •</p>						

